                    <comment id="12525006" author="fmeschbe" created="Wed, 5 Sep 2007 08:47:47 +0100"  >+1&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This would probably also benefit Sling, as I have my own implementation of the Mapper interface there because I read the descriptors using kxml, which is more light weight and has far less dependencies than Commons Digester. So I &amp;quot;stole&amp;quot; much of the code of the DigesterMapperImpl regarding descriptor verification ...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Also, removing the node type stuff from the DigesterMapper would remove the dependency on the Jackrabbit-Core package, which may or may not be available in certain use cases. Another reason, why I do not use the DigesterMapperImpl in Sling.</comment>
